#Text=The San Antonio Spurs ( 29 - 17 ) defeated the Milwaukee Bucks ( 22 - 22 ) 101 - 95 on Sunday at the AT & T Center in San Antonio .

#Text=Despite a strong first half where the Bucks out - scored the Spurs 55 - 47 , they were n't able to hold off the reigning NBA champion Spurs in the secondf , suffering a tough six - point loss on the road .
#Text=While the Bucks shot better from field and the three - point line , they were dominated at the free throw line where the Spurs went 26 - for - 30 and the Bucks finished just 9 - for - 13 .
#Text=The Bucks also committed 21 turnovers , which may have been another big difference in this game .
#Text=The Spurs had a strong showing from their frontcourt , as forwards Tim Duncan and Kawhi Leonard were the team - leaders in both points and rebounds .
#Text=In 31 minutes , Duncan finished with 20 points ( 9 - 13 FG , 2 - 2 FT ) and 11 rebounds , while Leonard had 19 points ( 4 - 11 FG , 1 - 5 3Pt , 10 - 12 FT ) and 14 rebounds in 36 minutes .
#Text=It was Leonard 's third double - double in his last four games , recording at least 14 rebounds in each of those matchups .
#Text=Tony Parker really struggled with his shot for the Spurs ( 3 - 13 FG , 0 - 2 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , but still contributed 10 points and five assists .
#Text=He 's now averaging 15 points and 5 assists on the season .
#Text=The Spurs did find some production off their bench , with two players finishing in double figures in points .
#Text=Boris Diaw had 14 points ( 7 - 11 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt ) and three rebounds , while Manu Ginobili finished with 13 points ( 3 - 8 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt , 6 - 8 FT ) and three assists .

#Text=Despite the loss , Kris Middleton played well , going 9 - for - 14 from the field and 3 - for - 5 from the three - point line to finish with 21 points and five rebounds as a starter at shooting guard .
#Text=He 's had two strong showings in a row , combining for 37 points , 12 rebounds and four steals over that span .
#Text=Jerryd Bayless played very well off the bench for the Bucks .
#Text=In 22 minutes , he added 15 points ( 5 - 10 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 5 - 7 FT ) and five assists , as he was very efficient with his time on the court .

#Text=Bayless had n't scored in double figures since the beginning of January , so it was good to see him turn things around on the offensive side of the ball and play well against a tough Spurs team .

#Text=Zaza Puchulia added 12 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 2 - 2 FT ) and six rebounds in 24 minutes , while Ersan Ilyasova finished with 11 points ( 4 - 8 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt , 2 - 4 FT ) and six rebounds in just over 22 minutes .
#Text=The Spurs ' next game will be at home against the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday , while the Bucks will travel to Miami to play the Heat on Tuesday .
